  {"title"=>"Worms", "description"=>"Quarterpipe, Funbox, Bank, Curb´s, Rail\nAm Bahnho einfach den Busbahnhof hochpushen dann durch den Park an den Drogensüchtigen vorbeilaufen.\nImmer geradeaus gehen der Eingang ist direkt neben einem Minigolfplatz.", "type"=>"", "lat"=>49.6385, "lng"=>8.35833, "slug"=>"worms", "obstacles"=>[]},
  {"title"=>"Mücheln", "description"=>"Miniramp\n...ein ruhig gelegener Skatepark neben einen Fußballplatz. Es sind kaum Skater auf den Park, obwohl es sich voll gut dort rollen lässt. Der Park beinhaltet ein Kicker, ne Funbox mit 2 Quarter und Rail, ne Miniramp, ne Miniramp und ne große Halfpipe, noch ne kleinere Funbox und eine Welle !!!! Ich versteh nicht warum bei dieser RIESEN Auswahl fast niemand dort ist !??! Weil so wenige darauf Skaten plant anscheinend die Stadt Mücheln alles wieder Platt zu machen! Die restlich noch rollenden Skater setzten sich mit aller Kraft dagengen ein ! Es wäre schön wenn wir den Park erhalten würden ....\nAm Arthur-Scheibener-Ring; neben Bolzplatz", "type"=>"Halfpipe\nMiniramp", "lat"=>51.2988, "lng"=>11.8156, "slug"=>"muecheln", "obstacles"=>[]},
  {"title"=>"Stockholm Brotherhood Plaza", "description"=>"Brotherhood Plaza is park project in Sweden. The park is about 43000 square feet or 4000 square meters and a bit more than half of the park is hard surface. The rest is grass islands within and around the plaza with park benches, barbacue places and open nature area.\n\n\n\nThe park does not look like your average skatepark, more like suburb, Barcelona-like structures and sculptures and small town-street spots. The park also has a over 20 meter wide spine bowl. The bowl has a 12 meter wide spine in two heights that you can skate on to and off of as a flatrail.\n\n\n\nBrotherhood is a by skaters for skaters construction firm and together with Stockholm City and most summer since 2006 they have been adding new spots to the plaza. Other people who wants to build DIY spots in the park are also welcomed and often get free material and help from Brotherhood to build what they want.\n\nThe goal for most spots on the plaza is to disguise them as real street spots and sculptures to make pics and video clips shot there look more like street than skatepark and to make the feeling of skating there more like street skate.\n\n\n\nDue to the Swedish weather its best to skate the plaza from late april to early october unless you are fine with cold weather. Some pictures below are from late december when its usually freezing and starts to snow.\n\n\n\nWhen it gets dark in the evening the plaza is lit up by 24 spotlights until 10 oclock at night.\n\n\n\nMore information and photos/videos on www.brotherhoodplaza.com or \"skate sverige\" on facebook\n\n\n\nContact:\n\nmail: plaza@brotherhood.se\n\nphone: +46 (0)70 8888 758\n\n\n\nBrotherhood firm is now considering building one or two large parks outside of Sweden so if your city wants to build a big and very original park they are welcome to get in touch.\n\n\nAt the Stockholm City T-central you get on the green subway line 17 to the end station Skarpnäck. At Skarpnäck (less than 20 minuite ride) you when you come out of the only exit you turn 90 degrees to the left and walk straight for one minuite and you will be on Brotherhood Plaza. Also see the map on www.map.brotherhoodplaza.com\n\n\n\n5-10 minutes walk from the plaza is Flaten lake which is a beautiful lake with cliffs to jump from, sand beach, forest and a 5 and 3 meter jumping tower. On the way to the lake is a metal fullpipe in a (no trespassing) industrial complex.\n\n\n\nSkating the plaza is free of charge and you are even allowed to camp/tent in the beautful nature area next to the plaza as long as one moves the tent a little bit every day so that it does not turn into a permanent camp site.\n\n\n\nFor people looking for hostels nearby we can suggest www.skanstulls.se which is 12 minutes away with the subway right in the chill south center bar and club district of Stockholm.\n\n\n\nWelcome over!\n\n\n\n", "type"=>"", "lat"=>59.2656, "lng"=>18.1362, "slug"=>"stockholm-brotherhood-plaza", "obstacles"=>[]},
